WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.503 --> 00:00:05.598
Narrator: <i>In the criminal justice
system. the people are represented</i>

2
00:00:05.639 --> 00:00:08.040
<i>by two separate yet
equally important groups...</i>

3
00:00:08.075 --> 00:00:09.941
<i>The police who
investigate crime.</i>

4
00:00:09.977 --> 00:00:12.947
<i>and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.</i>

5
00:00:12.980 --> 00:00:14.642
<i>These are their stories.</i>

6
00:00:18.185 --> 00:00:19.915
Paul!

7
00:00:19.953 --> 00:00:22.445
I had your office try you
at home this morning.

8
00:00:22.489 --> 00:00:24.515
You're still asking
for a severance.

9
00:00:24.558 --> 00:00:27.995
Yeah. Almost not. given the number of
threats my client received this weekend.

10
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:31.362
Diane. we prepped him for this. He
wavers now. we're back where we started.

11
00:00:31.398 --> 00:00:34.027
He's a kid... just the sight
of these two will freeze him.

12
00:00:34.067 --> 00:00:36.161
That's their right.
To intimidate him?

13
00:00:36.203 --> 00:00:39.139
We requested
separate transport vans.

14
00:00:39.172 --> 00:00:41.732
Hopefully this thing'll
be short and sweet.

15
00:00:57.891 --> 00:01:01.589
Bailiff: <i>Docket number 9357.</i>

16
00:01:01.628 --> 00:01:05.258
<i>Motion to sever
defendant Ryan M. Cutrona</i>

17
00:01:05.299 --> 00:01:07.530
<i>from co-defendants</i>

18
00:01:07.568 --> 00:01:12.268
<i>Howard S. Metzler
and Steven B. Hanauer.</i>

19
00:01:12.306 --> 00:01:15.140
Why is there a motion to
sever in a gang rape case now?

20
00:01:15.175 --> 00:01:18.111
Judge: <i>I'd like to get
this trial started. people.</i>

21
00:01:18.145 --> 00:01:19.636
<i>The more motions
filed on this case.</i>

22
00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:22.479
the more press
attention it seems to get.

23
00:01:22.516 --> 00:01:26.112
Due to an overwhelming amount of
evidence against his co-defendants...

24
00:01:26.153 --> 00:01:29.282
What evidence? He's
lying. He's got nothing.

25
00:01:29.323 --> 00:01:32.054
<i>He wants to save his own ass.</i>

26
00:01:32.092 --> 00:01:34.891
Judge: <i>Order!</i> Don't be
stupid. okay? Don't be dead.

27
00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:36.521
Order.

28
00:01:36.563 --> 00:01:38.031
We know what you did.

29
00:01:38.065 --> 00:01:39.658
<i>Okay. you hear me.
Ryan?</i> Judge: <i>Counsel!</i>

30
00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:42.329
(shouting) Judge: <i>I'll
have your client detained!</i>

31
00:01:42.369 --> 00:01:44.429
Look at me! Do you hear me?

32
00:01:44.471 --> 00:01:46.406
<i>Huh? You hear me?!</i>

33
00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:49.308
I want you to know exactly...!

34
00:01:49.343 --> 00:01:50.811
Wait. Ryan. don't...

35
00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:56.113
<i>(audience screaming. gun cocks)</i>

36
00:01:58.719 --> 00:02:00.312
Guard: Get down. get down!

37
00:02:02.055 --> 00:02:04.024
Face to the floor! Do it!

38
00:02:08.895 --> 00:02:11.888
<i>(theme music playing)</i>

39
00:03:36.249 --> 00:03:38.214
Because I can't even
get him to sit in a damn

40
00:03:38.238 --> 00:03:40.448
chair. much less listen
to anything I have to say.

41
00:03:40.487 --> 00:03:42.527
A severance is not going
to do your client much good

42
00:03:42.556 --> 00:03:44.582
if he's facing the
exact same charges.

43
00:03:44.624 --> 00:03:47.526
Oh. for crying...
The kid's terrified.

44
00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:50.690
I offered to lower the charges if
he gave me pertinent information.

45
00:03:50.731 --> 00:03:52.495
Okay. so where do we stand?

46
00:03:52.532 --> 00:03:55.001
I can prosecute either
way. with or without him.

47
00:03:55.035 --> 00:03:57.470
but I'd have to guess from
what happened in court

48
00:03:57.504 --> 00:03:59.405
that he's got
something of value.

49
00:03:59.439 --> 00:04:01.305
I'd rather have
the truth than not.

50
00:04:01.341 --> 00:04:03.401
Yeah. So let's set it up.

51
00:04:03.443 --> 00:04:05.002
We'll take a run at him.

52
00:04:05.045 --> 00:04:07.981
Logan: <i>Howard. how
long did you follow her for?</i>

53
00:04:08.014 --> 00:04:10.643
A couple blocks.

54
00:04:10.684 --> 00:04:13.153
<i>Did anybody talk about
it while you followed her?</i>

55
00:04:14.621 --> 00:04:17.318
We really didn't think
he'd go through with it.

56
00:04:17.357 --> 00:04:20.555
<i>Why? Did you
talk about it before?</i>

57
00:04:20.594 --> 00:04:22.563
<i>Yeah.</i>

58
00:04:22.596 --> 00:04:24.531
<i>Ryan said he wanted to.</i>

59
00:04:24.564 --> 00:04:27.329
<i>We just thought...
we'd set him up.</i>

60
00:04:27.367 --> 00:04:29.802
<i>he'd back off. get scared.</i>

61
00:04:29.836 --> 00:04:30.836
That's not true.

62
00:04:30.871 --> 00:04:32.863
Logan: <i>Did you touch
Ms. DeVries at all?</i>

63
00:04:32.906 --> 00:04:34.670
Lawyer: <i>We're clear
on that issue. Detective.</i>

64
00:04:34.708 --> 00:04:37.337
My client stated
that he only watched.

65
00:04:39.513 --> 00:04:41.607
Logan: <i>Did you
want to touch her?</i>

66
00:04:43.049 --> 00:04:45.348
Ryan's the one who got off.

67
00:04:49.189 --> 00:04:51.055
Hanauer's is worse.

68
00:04:51.091 --> 00:04:53.856
He says you begged him
to help you do someone.

69
00:04:53.894 --> 00:04:56.728
Says they even had to
stop you during the attack.

70
00:04:58.198 --> 00:04:59.996
I don't want to see it.

71
00:05:00.033 --> 00:05:01.763
It's just more lies.

72
00:05:01.802 --> 00:05:03.771
Why don't you fill us in?

73
00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:08.599
I can't.

74
00:05:08.642 --> 00:05:11.806
Ryan. whatever you're holding back
must be damning enough to scare them.

75
00:05:11.845 --> 00:05:14.212
They're counting on your
fear to protect themselves.

76
00:05:14.281 --> 00:05:16.807
I'll take a lie detector test...

77
00:05:16.850 --> 00:05:18.785
And <i>prove</i> that I
didn't do anything.

78
00:05:18.819 --> 00:05:21.345
That's not enough for what
your buddies are telling us.

79
00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:23.687
Ryan. you're accused
of raping a woman.

80
00:05:27.527 --> 00:05:29.519
I'm 17.

81
00:05:31.531 --> 00:05:34.626
I don't have a record.
You'll be tried as an adult.

82
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:36.728
Any jury that sees those tapes

83
00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:39.968
will send you up for a lot more
time than your buddies'll do.

84
00:05:47.581 --> 00:05:49.880
You know he didn't
run point on this.

85
00:05:49.916 --> 00:05:51.714
I can't prosecute on instincts.

86
00:05:51.751 --> 00:05:53.720
She had bruises on
her wrists and ankles.

87
00:05:53.753 --> 00:05:55.688
How many hands do
you think my client has?

88
00:05:55.722 --> 00:05:57.953
Interesting defense. You
plan to out-prosecute me?

89
00:05:57.991 --> 00:06:00.620
Where are you
going to take this?

90
00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:03.323
I can only work with
what I have on hand.

91
00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.229
and if your client plans to...

92
00:06:05.265 --> 00:06:08.861
martyr himself with a heavier
sentence. that's not my problem.

93
00:06:08.902 --> 00:06:12.395
I'll go after the others as
hard as I do your client.

94
00:06:12.439 --> 00:06:15.705
DNA tests on the semen
samples are due in this afternoon.

95
00:06:15.742 --> 00:06:17.802
We'll talk with you then.

96
00:06:19.646 --> 00:06:23.447
Because it's a game to these kids.
and I'm sure they were the driving force.

97
00:06:23.483 --> 00:06:26.749
The Cutrona kid's holding
something... I have no idea what it is.

98
00:06:26.786 --> 00:06:29.255
Nothing out of the
transcripts from the victim?

99
00:06:29.289 --> 00:06:31.656
Her recollection has
been shaky at best.

100
00:06:31.691 --> 00:06:34.354
She's pretty much
repressed the whole event.

101
00:06:36.496 --> 00:06:38.362
She's what. a reporter?

102
00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:41.425
Reporter? She
does exploitive crap!

103
00:06:41.468 --> 00:06:43.903
<i>All sizzle and no steak.</i>

104
00:06:43.937 --> 00:06:45.803
<i>Where is that coming from?</i>

105
00:06:45.839 --> 00:06:48.206
I'm sorry. Adam. but
I have to be honest.

106
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:50.710
I want to put away the
scum that raped her.

107
00:06:50.744 --> 00:06:54.579
but I don't have to embrace her
journalism. her lifestyle. her attitudes.

108
00:06:54.614 --> 00:06:57.641
I don't like her and I don't
think a jury'll like her either.

109
00:06:57.684 --> 00:07:00.176
Tough case without
her on the stand.

110
00:07:00.220 --> 00:07:03.088
I wish that were
my only concern.

111
00:07:03.123 --> 00:07:05.524
I feel like we're hitting
baseballs in the dark.

112
00:07:05.558 --> 00:07:08.995
We've got enough with the
tapes and maybe the circumstantial

113
00:07:09.029 --> 00:07:12.124
to put someone away...
Probably the wrong kid.

114
00:07:12.165 --> 00:07:14.293
Which means that Metzler's
and Hanauer's people

115
00:07:14.334 --> 00:07:16.428
<i>will ask to be severed
from the Cutrona kid</i>

116
00:07:16.469 --> 00:07:17.767
<i>because he'll take the fall.</i>

117
00:07:17.804 --> 00:07:20.000
then they get suspended
or greatly reduced.

118
00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:22.600
Or maybe nothing.

119
00:07:22.642 --> 00:07:24.873
No match on the semen sample.

120
00:07:24.911 --> 00:07:26.709
On any of them?

121
00:07:26.746 --> 00:07:30.012
That could solve our entire
dilemma. We may be dead in the water.

122
00:07:30.050 --> 00:07:31.951
Possibly another assailant?

123
00:07:31.985 --> 00:07:33.817
Never mentioned by the others.

124
00:07:33.853 --> 00:07:37.949
She was foggy the first few days on
the numbers. but since said it was three.

125
00:07:37.991 --> 00:07:41.291
What about a
boyfriend? I'll check.

126
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.699
Just a minute...

127
00:07:46.733 --> 00:07:49.567
Did she state whether there
was penetration during the rape?

128
00:07:49.602 --> 00:07:51.332
She's repressed it.

129
00:07:51.371 --> 00:07:54.398
Rape kit findings at the
hospital indicate there was.

130
00:07:54.441 --> 00:07:56.535
If there was no
discharge during the rape.

131
00:07:56.576 --> 00:07:59.171
could be a boyfriend...
Previous night. that morning.

132
00:07:59.212 --> 00:08:01.704
Well. find out.

133
00:08:01.748 --> 00:08:04.775
Either way. we're hurt
without a DNA match.

134
00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:09.088
Logan: <i>Paul!</i>

135
00:08:09.122 --> 00:08:11.751
We're thinking of
requisitioning you

136
00:08:11.791 --> 00:08:13.919
a flak jacket for your birthday.

137
00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.792
Yeah. it's all
over the precinct.

138
00:08:15.829 --> 00:08:18.107
Last I heard he... what.
single-handedly disarmed the kid?

139
00:08:18.131 --> 00:08:20.828
Crushed the gun
with his bare hands.

140
00:08:29.309 --> 00:08:31.301
Monica DeVries have a boyfriend?

141
00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:33.142
Don't know. Why.
are you in the market?

142
00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:35.680
How was she in the line-up?

143
00:08:37.384 --> 00:08:39.353
What do you mean?

144
00:08:39.386 --> 00:08:41.150
Her confidence.

145
00:08:41.187 --> 00:08:44.521
Not good. she wasn't
clear. And the perps?

146
00:08:44.557 --> 00:08:46.924
<i>The young kid was
a giveaway. nervous.</i>

147
00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:48.622
He'd never been in a line-up.

148
00:08:50.296 --> 00:08:52.197
Is this thing unraveling?

149
00:08:52.232 --> 00:08:55.862
There's no DNA match
on the semen samples.

150
00:08:55.902 --> 00:08:58.770
Come on. that's crap! They bragged
about it all over the neighborhood.

151
00:08:58.805 --> 00:09:00.273
We got their confession on tape!

152
00:09:00.306 --> 00:09:02.002
Conflicting.

153
00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:03.977
Yeah...

154
00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:05.911
still.

155
00:09:07.947 --> 00:09:10.678
So there's no match... that
doesn't mean she wasn't raped.

156
00:09:12.952 --> 00:09:14.716
What are you gonna do?

157
00:09:16.122 --> 00:09:18.387
Hope she slept with
someone before the attack.

158
00:09:23.463 --> 00:09:25.659
Four in the last half hour.

159
00:09:25.698 --> 00:09:28.065
Press thinks the case
may be slipping away.

160
00:09:28.101 --> 00:09:30.246
How do you think they'd react
if they sensed an opportunity

161
00:09:30.270 --> 00:09:32.364
to publicly fry
one of their own?

162
00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:33.703
Meaning what?

163
00:09:35.341 --> 00:09:37.333
Advance copy of
tomorrow's "Ledger."

164
00:09:40.947 --> 00:09:43.610
This backed up? They
know she's got a record.

165
00:09:43.650 --> 00:09:46.882
A five-year-old bust. She
was there to research a story.

166
00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:48.230
Can't we counter
with a statement?

167
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:51.656
Like what? "Everybody
past fifth grade

168
00:09:51.691 --> 00:09:53.717
should understand relevance"?

169
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:57.219
Reasonable doubt in the mind
of a jury. the defense'll run with it.

170
00:09:58.965 --> 00:10:01.059
One drug arrest five years ago.

171
00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:04.697
It's like another lifetime. But
now. because it's on page six.

172
00:10:04.737 --> 00:10:06.638
I can be raped without penalty.

173
00:10:06.673 --> 00:10:09.040
It's not a question
of abstract application

174
00:10:09.075 --> 00:10:11.306
of the law. Ms.
DeVries. it's perception.

175
00:10:11.344 --> 00:10:15.008
<i>We're dealing with the collective
minds and morals of a jury.</i>

176
00:10:15.048 --> 00:10:17.449
Often. it's just a question
of cause and effect.

177
00:10:17.484 --> 00:10:20.477
What was she doing down there?
Why was she dressed like that?

178
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.217
And what's her background?
Jurors are not computers.

179
00:10:23.256 --> 00:10:25.521
these things do have
an impact on them.

180
00:10:25.558 --> 00:10:27.823
Maybe they'd like to
check between my toes

181
00:10:27.861 --> 00:10:30.023
for needle marks
before they rule.

182
00:10:30.063 --> 00:10:32.157
I'll pass.

183
00:10:32.198 --> 00:10:34.429
I've already been
bent over once.

184
00:10:41.040 --> 00:10:44.670
Unfortunately. we can no longer
prosecute without you on the stand.

185
00:10:44.711 --> 00:10:48.910
You told me you had no problem
with me being off the stand.

186
00:10:48.948 --> 00:10:51.247
that the drug arrest
might cloud the issue.

187
00:10:51.284 --> 00:10:54.413
In a perfect world it would. but
your friends in the fourth estate

188
00:10:54.454 --> 00:10:56.787
have taken that
choice out of our hands.

189
00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:59.759
Plus... we didn't get a
match on the DNA tests.

190
00:10:59.792 --> 00:11:01.784
What?! <i>Do you have a boyfriend?</i>

191
00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:04.195
Someone you might have
slept with before the attack?

192
00:11:05.732 --> 00:11:08.759
What the hell does that matter?
Does that mean I wasn't raped?

193
00:11:08.801 --> 00:11:10.997
The defense'll probably
ask for a blood sample.

194
00:11:11.037 --> 00:11:14.201
From every guy they think
I might have had sex with?

195
00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:16.732
Monica. I don't want
to diminish the rape.

196
00:11:16.776 --> 00:11:19.575
but you're a reporter.
try processing the facts.

197
00:11:19.612 --> 00:11:22.776
If it's the system you
abhor. make the decision.

198
00:11:22.815 --> 00:11:26.513
Do you want these people who
violated you to walk uncontested?

199
00:11:28.454 --> 00:11:30.616
No one in this
room has the ability

200
00:11:30.657 --> 00:11:32.853
to redesign the entire railroad.

201
00:11:32.892 --> 00:11:36.090
So I should just lash myself
to the front of the train?

202
00:11:36.129 --> 00:11:38.621
Make my peers really happy.

203
00:11:38.665 --> 00:11:40.964
Give them a lot to write about.

204
00:11:42.135 --> 00:11:43.569
You think this is
enough newsprint

205
00:11:43.603 --> 00:11:46.539
dedicated to one
rape investigation?

206
00:11:46.573 --> 00:11:49.304
Everything but my
name... How polite of them.

207
00:11:49.342 --> 00:11:51.902
There's enough newsprint
that if you don't testify.

208
00:11:51.945 --> 00:11:54.642
you're sending a dangerous
message to the women of this city...

209
00:11:54.681 --> 00:11:58.675
<i>That a rape victim's
chances for justice are so slim.</i>

210
00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:00.846
<i>she might as well not
even press charges.</i>

211
00:12:03.323 --> 00:12:06.316
You are a public figure.
People do watch what you do.

212
00:12:07.694 --> 00:12:09.560
<i>It's difficult for any woman.</i>

213
00:12:09.596 --> 00:12:12.691
I'd be lying to myself if I
thought it was easier for you.

214
00:12:15.134 --> 00:12:17.660
Testifying might be the
only way to counter this.

215
00:12:25.645 --> 00:12:27.671
"The Post." "The Times."

216
00:12:27.714 --> 00:12:29.342
everything to "Vanity Fair."

217
00:12:29.382 --> 00:12:31.977
She's right...
Everybody's taken a shot.

218
00:12:32.018 --> 00:12:34.214
She's not named. but
she's well-known enough

219
00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:36.621
so the description does
just as much damage.

220
00:12:38.558 --> 00:12:40.618
Who provided the most coverage?

221
00:12:40.660 --> 00:12:42.185
"Post."

222
00:12:42.228 --> 00:12:43.992
You know anyone over there?

223
00:12:44.030 --> 00:12:46.124
One or two people. why?

224
00:12:46.165 --> 00:12:48.794
We need as much
background on her as possible.

225
00:12:48.835 --> 00:12:50.997
You think she's still using?

226
00:12:52.505 --> 00:12:55.942
If she is. I'd like to know
before the rest of the world does.

227
00:12:57.543 --> 00:12:59.307
Thank you.

228
00:13:00.546 --> 00:13:02.879
Lunch? Thanks a lot.

229
00:13:02.915 --> 00:13:05.043
Look. the bottom line is.

230
00:13:05.084 --> 00:13:07.519
nobody's gone too far.

231
00:13:07.553 --> 00:13:09.613
Every news source in
town has practically ID'd her.

232
00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:11.386
No more than any
other rape victim.

233
00:13:11.424 --> 00:13:13.689
"Well-known investigative
reporter for local TV

234
00:13:13.726 --> 00:13:16.821
whose oft-criticized style of
sensational and exploitive coverage..."

235
00:13:16.863 --> 00:13:19.958
Listen. man. she's a
local minor celebrity.

236
00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:21.524
people want to follow the case.

237
00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:24.969
The need to read drives the press
to print speculations like a drug habit?

238
00:13:25.004 --> 00:13:26.996
Can I put it this
way? Nobody I know

239
00:13:27.040 --> 00:13:29.236
is afraid of a
civil suit for libel.

240
00:13:29.275 --> 00:13:30.800
She says she's clean.

241
00:13:30.843 --> 00:13:33.745
Plus. I talked to her producers...
They verified the assignment.

242
00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:35.942
Her producers? What
are they going to say?

243
00:13:35.982 --> 00:13:38.747
She's a commodity. man. You
think they're going to burn her?

244
00:13:38.785 --> 00:13:40.913
But her peers will?

245
00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:42.387
Her peers?

246
00:13:42.422 --> 00:13:44.687
Maybe her peers think
she got what she deserved.

247
00:13:44.724 --> 00:13:48.252
Why? Because they think she was
buying or because they think she's a bitch?

248
00:13:49.562 --> 00:13:53.226
Look. I'm not here to
make any accusations.

249
00:13:53.266 --> 00:13:57.226
but if you listen to what
the hallway rumors are.

250
00:13:57.270 --> 00:14:00.035
that's what she
was down there for.

251
00:14:04.811 --> 00:14:07.406
Stone: How many assailants
were there. Ms. DeVries?

252
00:14:07.447 --> 00:14:09.939
<i>There were three.</i> And
did all <i>three</i> of these men

253
00:14:09.982 --> 00:14:12.679
attempt to engage in sexual
acts with you on that day?

254
00:14:12.719 --> 00:14:14.847
I think so. You
originally told police

255
00:14:14.887 --> 00:14:17.914
there may have been as many
as five assailants. is that not true?

256
00:14:17.957 --> 00:14:21.223
I was confused... The hospital
reports that you were traumatized.

257
00:14:21.260 --> 00:14:23.695
and suffering from trauma-induced
amnesia. is that correct?

258
00:14:23.730 --> 00:14:25.858
Yes. that's right. Yet
<i>you remember now?</i>

259
00:14:25.898 --> 00:14:28.265
Yes! You remember the
day and the time of day?

260
00:14:28.301 --> 00:14:31.601
How warm it was? So warm
you wanted to take your jacket off.

261
00:14:31.637 --> 00:14:34.106
You remember the stoop
that they forced you under.

262
00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:36.166
screaming for help.
and begging for mercy?

263
00:14:36.209 --> 00:14:40.044
Yes. that's right. Yet you cannot remember
how many men tried to have sex with you?!

264
00:14:40.079 --> 00:14:41.513
That's not the same thing!

265
00:14:41.547 --> 00:14:43.311
Did <i>any</i> of these men
try have sex with you?

266
00:14:43.349 --> 00:14:45.944
Yes. damn it! Then will you
submit to a drug test. Ms. DeVries?

267
00:14:45.985 --> 00:14:48.045
What the hell is going on?

268
00:14:48.087 --> 00:14:50.682
At that point. I'd jump
up and yell objection.

269
00:14:52.658 --> 00:14:54.388
And then what would happen?

270
00:14:54.427 --> 00:14:56.020
I'd argue relevance.

271
00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:59.089
the defense would state that
you were there to buy drugs.

272
00:14:59.132 --> 00:15:02.193
or already under
the influence of them.

273
00:15:02.235 --> 00:15:04.534
Thus your recall...

274
00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:06.869
Or your actions...

275
00:15:06.906 --> 00:15:09.740
Were radically different
from what we're stating.

276
00:15:10.743 --> 00:15:12.371
And you would say?

277
00:15:12.412 --> 00:15:14.506
I don't know.

278
00:15:14.547 --> 00:15:17.107
Why don't you tell me?

279
00:15:19.218 --> 00:15:22.382
Word has it. your habit is
not as old as you'd like to think.

280
00:15:25.825 --> 00:15:27.794
I was not high.

281
00:15:35.501 --> 00:15:36.560
(sighs)

282
00:15:37.703 --> 00:15:39.831
Okay. that's a start.

283
00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:50.613
Were you there to buy drugs?

284
00:15:51.918 --> 00:15:53.614
I was raped.

285
00:15:53.653 --> 00:15:56.817
What the hell difference does
it make why I was down there?

286
00:15:56.856 --> 00:15:58.154
<i>It doesn't.</i>

287
00:15:58.191 --> 00:16:01.457
I don't care if you were
there to buy a nuclear bomb.

288
00:16:02.495 --> 00:16:04.396
You are not on trial.

289
00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:07.930
But I cannot
prosecute effectively

290
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:10.732
if I have to worry what's
around every corner.

291
00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:22.444
I asked them if they
had any coke for sale.

292
00:16:22.482 --> 00:16:25.611
Them... the boys who raped you?

293
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:26.983
It was for the story.

294
00:16:27.987 --> 00:16:29.979
To check on availability.

295
00:16:39.732 --> 00:16:41.724
Hurts us that she
initiated contact.

296
00:16:41.767 --> 00:16:44.498
The defense'll state it
could have been a come on.

297
00:16:44.537 --> 00:16:47.939
That's beatable if the jury buys

298
00:16:47.974 --> 00:16:50.307
that her request for
coke was research.

299
00:16:50.343 --> 00:16:51.936
Do you? No...

300
00:16:51.978 --> 00:16:53.674
But I don't have any choice.

301
00:16:53.713 --> 00:16:55.944
It's her memory I'm
concerned about now.

302
00:16:55.982 --> 00:16:58.281
Her recollection on
a lot of the details

303
00:16:58.317 --> 00:16:59.979
did feel... co-mingled.

304
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:02.318
Could have been
culled from the papers.

305
00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.881
Yeah. too good on some.
non-existent on others.

306
00:17:04.924 --> 00:17:07.723
She remembered she scratched
someone. that her actual memory?

307
00:17:09.328 --> 00:17:11.263
"I remember...

308
00:17:11.297 --> 00:17:13.266
clawing at a sweaty face."

309
00:17:13.299 --> 00:17:16.758
Police report does not list
scratches on any of the accused.

310
00:17:16.802 --> 00:17:19.033
and there was no tissue
under her fingernails.

311
00:17:19.071 --> 00:17:22.473
And "The Post" and another paper
both describe that in portrayal pieces.

312
00:17:24.911 --> 00:17:27.312
She hadn't talked
to any reporters.

313
00:17:28.548 --> 00:17:31.643
They took license.
did not present as fact.

314
00:17:31.684 --> 00:17:34.381
and she latched onto that.

315
00:17:34.420 --> 00:17:36.855
Do you think it was
a conscious attempt?

316
00:17:36.889 --> 00:17:38.585
My best guess. no.

317
00:17:38.624 --> 00:17:40.593
I'd say she's
filling in the blanks.

318
00:17:40.626 --> 00:17:42.686
and what better source
than news accounts?

319
00:17:44.697 --> 00:17:47.257
It makes her a
liability on the stand.

320
00:17:47.300 --> 00:17:50.270
Which means we better
find out one way or the other.

321
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:58.639
At this point. she had no
recollection of the event at all?

322
00:17:58.678 --> 00:18:02.115
She knew what had happened to
her. but only because she had been told.

323
00:18:02.148 --> 00:18:04.640
And she was still
in physical pain.

324
00:18:06.052 --> 00:18:08.886
Any rule of thumb on how
much usually comes back?

325
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:11.288
It differs case to case.

326
00:18:11.324 --> 00:18:12.724
Best hope scenario.

327
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:16.251
Usually the mind
will only go so far.

328
00:18:16.295 --> 00:18:18.890
It'll fill in the areas
of information

329
00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:21.628
around the assault.
but it won't go

330
00:18:21.667 --> 00:18:24.466
all the way back into the pain.

331
00:18:25.471 --> 00:18:27.633
Thanks.

332
00:18:27.673 --> 00:18:30.472
If we put her on the
stand now. they'll shred us.

333
00:18:33.212 --> 00:18:34.578
I don't know.

334
00:18:34.614 --> 00:18:36.947
The public hears dismissal.

335
00:18:36.983 --> 00:18:39.111
they think the case
has been dropped.

336
00:18:39.151 --> 00:18:41.643
We'll be editorialized
from hell to breakfast.

337
00:18:41.687 --> 00:18:43.883
I'll re-file as soon
as something breaks.

338
00:18:43.923 --> 00:18:46.552
Yeah. well. they won't
let you finish the sentence.

339
00:18:46.592 --> 00:18:49.084
The press hears dismissal.

340
00:18:49.128 --> 00:18:50.562
that's it.

341
00:18:50.596 --> 00:18:52.064
Then you tell me what to do.

342
00:18:52.098 --> 00:18:54.499
The judicial calendar has
already been announced.

343
00:18:54.533 --> 00:18:57.025
Who did you draw? Scanlon.

344
00:18:57.069 --> 00:18:59.595
Tough on rape. could
have done worse.

345
00:18:59.639 --> 00:19:02.040
Adam. she had poor recall

346
00:19:02.074 --> 00:19:04.634
in the mock cross.
and her own doctor

347
00:19:04.677 --> 00:19:06.805
doubts the details
have returned.

348
00:19:06.846 --> 00:19:09.111
That. combined with
the drug use rumor.

349
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:11.117
The fact that she
asked about coke.

350
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:14.177
whether it was research or not.
puts her in a pretty negative light.

351
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.348
What about the gun
charge on Metzler?

352
00:19:16.389 --> 00:19:19.382
Criminal possession. third
degree. he never even fired it.

353
00:19:19.425 --> 00:19:22.452
He had intent but. with three
court officers wrestling for control...

354
00:19:22.495 --> 00:19:25.055
That's an "E" felony. Would
you rather let him walk?

355
00:19:25.097 --> 00:19:26.725
It's his first offense.

356
00:19:26.766 --> 00:19:28.792
They'll plead to a
class "A" misdemeanor.

357
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:31.030
he'll walk and then we'll
really look desperate.

358
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:33.039
Whew! <i>We'll hold it.</i>

359
00:19:33.072 --> 00:19:35.234
We'll tack it on
the rape if we get it.

360
00:19:35.274 --> 00:19:37.140
All right. you just
do me the favor.

361
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.304
and you go as fast
as you can to re-open.

362
00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:41.905
We'll get Greevey and Logan
back on the investigation.

363
00:19:41.947 --> 00:19:44.507
They'll find evidence to
open up the Cutrona kid.

364
00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:46.018
It lies with him.

365
00:19:46.052 --> 00:19:48.749
Somebody's gotta
talk to Monica DeVries.

366
00:19:49.955 --> 00:19:52.117
Stone: <i>We go into
trial now and we lose.</i>

367
00:19:52.158 --> 00:19:54.127
<i>we cannot go after
them again ever.</i>

368
00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:02.126
You asked me what I
thought the odds were.

369
00:20:02.168 --> 00:20:04.160
I'm giving you a
fair assessment.

370
00:20:04.203 --> 00:20:06.502
It'll be swept into
some pending file.

371
00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.804
Robinette: <i>Monica. we're
not dropping the case.</i>

372
00:20:08.841 --> 00:20:11.333
Oh. and we'll have a better
chance two months from now?

373
00:20:11.377 --> 00:20:14.609
Hopefully we can go in with
more substantive evidence.

374
00:20:14.647 --> 00:20:17.742
What more could you possibly
need? They've confessed!

375
00:20:17.783 --> 00:20:19.911
I need you on the stand
and I can't put you there.

376
00:20:19.952 --> 00:20:22.615
I agreed. for God's sake.

377
00:20:22.655 --> 00:20:24.283
You don't remember.

378
00:20:24.323 --> 00:20:26.155
What?

379
00:20:26.192 --> 00:20:28.024
You don't remember the events.

380
00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:31.260
Your mind has picked up on a mixture of
facts and speculation from the news media

381
00:20:31.297 --> 00:20:34.426
and blended them together
into something that you believe.

382
00:20:34.467 --> 00:20:36.959
But if I put you on the stand.

383
00:20:37.002 --> 00:20:38.664
any defense
attorney in this city

384
00:20:38.704 --> 00:20:41.799
will blow enough holes
in that case to bury us.

385
00:20:41.841 --> 00:20:44.208
What matters
is that they did it.

386
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:46.041
Yes. that matters.

387
00:20:46.078 --> 00:20:48.570
But the three of us
knowing that in this room

388
00:20:48.614 --> 00:20:50.515
is not a substitute for proof.

389
00:20:50.549 --> 00:20:53.951
And I do intend to prove that
you were raped by these suspects.

390
00:20:58.324 --> 00:21:01.658
Bailiff: <i>Docket number 9357.</i>

391
00:21:01.694 --> 00:21:03.686
motion to dismiss

392
00:21:03.729 --> 00:21:06.790
<i>in People versus
Howard S. Metzler.</i>

393
00:21:06.832 --> 00:21:08.926
<i>Steven B. Hanauer.</i>

394
00:21:08.968 --> 00:21:11.130
<i>Ryan M. Cutrona.</i>

395
00:21:11.170 --> 00:21:12.638
Mr. Robinette.

396
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:17.702
Your Honor. with respect
to the People's motion.

397
00:21:17.743 --> 00:21:21.305
I'd like to reiterate the State's
intention to reopen this case

398
00:21:21.347 --> 00:21:24.112
on such a date when
further evidence is obtained.

399
00:21:24.150 --> 00:21:27.314
Otherwise. the People's
position is clearly stated

400
00:21:27.353 --> 00:21:29.549
in the papers filed earlier.

401
00:21:29.588 --> 00:21:32.422
Your comments are
so noted. Mr. Robinette.

402
00:21:35.227 --> 00:21:38.686
Case number 9357 is dismissed.

403
00:21:38.731 --> 00:21:40.791
<i>Defendants are free to go.</i>

404
00:21:40.833 --> 00:21:42.233
<i>(gavel bangs)</i>

405
00:22:04.456 --> 00:22:06.448
<i>(cameras clicking)</i>

406
00:22:11.564 --> 00:22:13.294
I'd just like to get this case

407
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:15.460
back up and running
as quickly as possible.

408
00:22:15.501 --> 00:22:18.198
If it sits. we run the risk
of it collapsing completely.

409
00:22:18.237 --> 00:22:20.263
and this case is
not un-winnable.

410
00:22:20.306 --> 00:22:22.468
Wait a minute. we gave
you enough to prosecute.

411
00:22:22.508 --> 00:22:24.534
We're not the ones
who blew this thing.

412
00:22:24.577 --> 00:22:28.275
This is not an assessment of blame. It's
a petition to put the case back together.

413
00:22:28.314 --> 00:22:30.510
We've got a victim who's
co-mingling fact and fiction.

414
00:22:30.549 --> 00:22:33.417
and a defendant who's holding
back relevant information.

415
00:22:33.452 --> 00:22:34.818
So how do we get the truth?

416
00:22:34.854 --> 00:22:36.823
You made the
motion to dismiss...

417
00:22:36.856 --> 00:22:38.484
you got any ideas?

418
00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:41.119
No. I don't have any
ideas! That's why I'm here!

419
00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:44.722
All right. fellas. could we please
hold this down to a dull head stomp?

420
00:22:44.763 --> 00:22:46.664
We're thin.

421
00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:49.066
It's obvious they're
holding something back.

422
00:22:49.101 --> 00:22:52.128
If we weren't confident you
could provide that something for us.

423
00:22:52.171 --> 00:22:54.766
we would've taken
our shots with the jury.

424
00:22:54.807 --> 00:22:57.174
As for suggestions. I
don't have any ideas.

425
00:22:57.209 --> 00:22:59.371
<i>We weren't able to
leverage Hanauer.</i>

426
00:22:59.411 --> 00:23:02.074
<i>or Metzler. and the younger
kid is not forthcoming.</i>

427
00:23:02.114 --> 00:23:05.516
And he's not going to give it up
now that the case has been dismissed.

428
00:23:05.551 --> 00:23:06.917
But...

429
00:23:06.952 --> 00:23:08.784
if you guys can
find a back door...

430
00:23:08.821 --> 00:23:12.155
Well. maybe we press
the two older kids...

431
00:23:12.191 --> 00:23:14.717
Work some kind
of a play on them.

432
00:23:18.530 --> 00:23:20.590
We'll backtrack
through our notes.

433
00:23:20.633 --> 00:23:22.192
see what pops up.

434
00:23:25.004 --> 00:23:26.666
All right. three weeks.

435
00:23:26.705 --> 00:23:29.004
that's all I can afford
with their caseload.

436
00:23:29.041 --> 00:23:30.942
Thanks.

437
00:23:33.312 --> 00:23:35.543
Personal effects.
Monica DeVries.

438
00:23:35.581 --> 00:23:37.482
She never picked them up.

439
00:23:37.516 --> 00:23:40.247
Never will. either.
Reminds her too much.

440
00:23:40.286 --> 00:23:41.982
I can't say as I blame her.

441
00:23:42.021 --> 00:23:44.422
Mind if I borrow this?

442
00:23:44.456 --> 00:23:47.426
Oh. no. Paul. We have our own.

443
00:23:53.332 --> 00:23:54.823
All right.

444
00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:57.336
They stopped here around
3:50 in the afternoon.

445
00:23:57.369 --> 00:23:59.770
They forced her
down under that stoop.

446
00:23:59.805 --> 00:24:02.206
<i>General disagreement
on who said what.</i>

447
00:24:02.241 --> 00:24:03.470
<i>blouse was ripped off.</i>

448
00:24:03.509 --> 00:24:06.673
<i>jacket pulled up to
hold her arms until it rips.</i>

449
00:24:06.712 --> 00:24:09.204
<i>Slight shoulder
dislocation during struggle.</i>

450
00:24:09.248 --> 00:24:11.183
<i>The... well.</i>

451
00:24:11.216 --> 00:24:13.082
now we get into
a big discrepancy

452
00:24:13.118 --> 00:24:16.987
as to who was
actually on top of her.

453
00:24:17.022 --> 00:24:18.422
ER report...

454
00:24:18.457 --> 00:24:20.323
Multiple attackers.

455
00:24:20.359 --> 00:24:22.260
How many of these
buildings did we canvas?

456
00:24:22.294 --> 00:24:25.059
We canvassed both sides...

457
00:24:25.097 --> 00:24:27.089
Whole block. came
up with nothing.

458
00:24:27.132 --> 00:24:29.226
No witnesses. just
a lot of listeners.

459
00:24:29.268 --> 00:24:31.100
It's the post Kitty
Genovese era.

460
00:24:31.136 --> 00:24:33.662
No one wants to look. they
think they'll get involved.

461
00:24:33.706 --> 00:24:35.504
This building and
the one next to it.

462
00:24:35.541 --> 00:24:38.340
weren't there a couple of
apartments we never got?

463
00:24:42.047 --> 00:24:44.175
Yeah. 1B. right here.

464
00:24:44.216 --> 00:24:46.151
Fifth. sixth and 11th.

465
00:24:46.185 --> 00:24:49.121
Left notes each time.
Upstairs. same thing.

466
00:24:49.154 --> 00:24:51.783
Good a place as any.

467
00:24:51.824 --> 00:24:54.794
It's about the rape
that happened out front.

468
00:24:54.827 --> 00:24:56.352
Woman: <i>I was gone.</i>

469
00:24:56.395 --> 00:24:58.023
<i>Upstate at my sister's.</i>

470
00:24:58.063 --> 00:25:01.158
Did you hear anything from any
of the neighbors about that day?

471
00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:03.032
You still haven't caught them?

472
00:25:03.068 --> 00:25:05.162
Logan: <i>Hey. Max.
let me get in here.</i>

473
00:25:07.506 --> 00:25:09.873
Yes. ma'am. we have.
We're just following up.

474
00:25:09.908 --> 00:25:12.537
We're wondering. did you
hear anything since then?

475
00:25:12.578 --> 00:25:13.807
Talk. rumors?

476
00:25:13.846 --> 00:25:15.838
I don't go out.

477
00:25:15.881 --> 00:25:18.350
This is as far out
in the world as I go

478
00:25:18.384 --> 00:25:20.478
without my son. <i>(lock clicks)</i>

479
00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:22.750
You better believe
I wasn't at home.

480
00:25:22.788 --> 00:25:24.689
20 hours of labor.

481
00:25:24.723 --> 00:25:27.852
Besides. I called. I left a
message at the number you left.

482
00:25:29.628 --> 00:25:31.654
(sighs) We never got it.

483
00:25:31.697 --> 00:25:34.895
What a surprise. Ms. Varella.
was there any talk in the building

484
00:25:34.933 --> 00:25:36.834
about what people heard or saw?

485
00:25:36.869 --> 00:25:40.306
Yeah. there were more people here in one
weekend than I've talked to in two years.

486
00:25:40.339 --> 00:25:42.604
How come you
only arrested three?

487
00:25:42.641 --> 00:25:44.405
Why? Do you think
there was more?

488
00:25:44.443 --> 00:25:46.537
The guy down in "C." Silva.

489
00:25:46.578 --> 00:25:49.343
heard the whole thing.
Said it was six or seven?

490
00:25:49.381 --> 00:25:52.283
Well... wasn't it?

491
00:25:53.452 --> 00:25:55.080
(chirping)

492
00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:57.021
I heard the case was dismissed.

493
00:25:57.056 --> 00:25:59.651
That doesn't mean it's closed.

494
00:25:59.691 --> 00:26:01.785
Did you hear the
rape. Mr. Silva?

495
00:26:01.827 --> 00:26:03.557
Most of it.

496
00:26:03.595 --> 00:26:06.087
Although I wasn't sure
what was going on.

497
00:26:06.131 --> 00:26:08.327
I mean...

498
00:26:08.367 --> 00:26:10.461
this street.

499
00:26:10.502 --> 00:26:13.870
Didn't we talk to you? We
got a statement down from you.

500
00:26:15.541 --> 00:26:17.407
I said that I was gone.

501
00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:23.442
I was... going through something

502
00:26:23.482 --> 00:26:25.644
with a friend of mine.

503
00:26:25.684 --> 00:26:27.880
I didn't want him
to know I was here.

504
00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:29.513
(huffs)

505
00:26:29.555 --> 00:26:32.047
You didn't call 911
during the attack?

506
00:26:32.091 --> 00:26:34.083
I wasn't sure at first.

507
00:26:34.126 --> 00:26:35.526
Uh...

508
00:26:35.561 --> 00:26:37.621
I know I was wrong not to.

509
00:26:37.663 --> 00:26:40.428
<i>These kids live around here.</i>

510
00:26:40.466 --> 00:26:43.925
You know how much
bashing goes on on this block?

511
00:26:45.204 --> 00:26:46.763
Besides...

512
00:26:46.805 --> 00:26:48.899
I heard you were
making arrests. so...

513
00:26:48.941 --> 00:26:51.638
How many people did you hear?

514
00:26:51.677 --> 00:26:54.112
I thought I might have heard...

515
00:26:54.146 --> 00:26:56.206
five.

516
00:26:57.850 --> 00:26:59.341
I. uh... I-I...

517
00:26:59.384 --> 00:27:01.649
I guess I might
have heard three.

518
00:27:04.857 --> 00:27:07.588
I tell you. it's more of a mess
now than it was two months ago.

519
00:27:07.626 --> 00:27:10.960
People don't know what they heard.
what they saw. what they didn't see.

520
00:27:10.996 --> 00:27:14.865
what they heard on the news. what they
heard on the street. in the newspapers.

521
00:27:14.900 --> 00:27:17.335
Maybe we'll get a guy
down here with a gold watch.

522
00:27:17.369 --> 00:27:19.133
hypnotizes the
whole neighborhood?

523
00:27:21.607 --> 00:27:23.075
What?

524
00:27:24.610 --> 00:27:27.341
Why don't we take a
legitimate shot with the vic?

525
00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:31.145
Come on. Mike. It's
a weak case as is.

526
00:27:31.183 --> 00:27:34.711
You know how the courts stand
on that. Hit and miss at best.

527
00:27:34.753 --> 00:27:38.520
No. no. no. I'm not saying we provide
them with hypnotically-induced testimony.

528
00:27:38.557 --> 00:27:40.890
No. we'll use it for
investigation only.

529
00:27:45.564 --> 00:27:47.328
Talk to the DA.

530
00:27:50.903 --> 00:27:52.895
Robinette: <i>They
don't always toss it.</i>

531
00:27:52.938 --> 00:27:56.136
but they have been uneven
in accepting aided testimony.

532
00:27:56.175 --> 00:27:58.610
I know that. That's
not what we're asking.

533
00:27:58.644 --> 00:28:00.613
Look. we're up
against a wall here.

534
00:28:00.646 --> 00:28:02.342
I don't want to put her under.

535
00:28:02.381 --> 00:28:04.179
have a new
investigatory line pop.

536
00:28:04.216 --> 00:28:06.776
then have the courts tell
you guys we can't use it.

537
00:28:08.353 --> 00:28:11.050
It's a good idea... try
it. but if anything new

538
00:28:11.089 --> 00:28:13.923
surfaces during the
session. we've got to link it

539
00:28:13.959 --> 00:28:16.360
to something
substantive down the line.

540
00:28:16.395 --> 00:28:18.694
As testimony. I'd
rather not use it at all.

541
00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:20.528
unless it's
extremely compelling.

542
00:28:21.967 --> 00:28:23.959
We'll let you know.

543
00:28:30.943 --> 00:28:32.775
We got bad news.

544
00:28:33.812 --> 00:28:35.713
It's the tox report.

545
00:28:35.747 --> 00:28:38.717
She left a brush and some other
effects with the police after the rape.

546
00:28:38.750 --> 00:28:41.777
The hair tested positive. but...

547
00:28:41.820 --> 00:28:43.550
We can probably counter it.

548
00:28:43.589 --> 00:28:45.888
It doesn't mean she
was using on that day.

549
00:28:52.030 --> 00:28:54.431
Paul. you made a
serious mistake here.

550
00:28:55.734 --> 00:28:58.363
You ordered a lab
test on what basis?

551
00:29:00.439 --> 00:29:02.135
It's for our knowledge only.

552
00:29:02.174 --> 00:29:04.040
I don't want to
prosecute her on it.

553
00:29:05.611 --> 00:29:07.876
What about her right to privacy?

554
00:29:07.913 --> 00:29:09.779
Wait a minute.

555
00:29:09.815 --> 00:29:11.545
This is one of your
biggest concerns.

556
00:29:11.583 --> 00:29:14.075
"Let's find out before the
rest of the world does."

557
00:29:14.119 --> 00:29:16.145
That is over the line.

558
00:29:17.990 --> 00:29:20.152
You mean to tell me
it's more important

559
00:29:20.192 --> 00:29:22.320
that we maintain some
myth of blind justice.

560
00:29:22.361 --> 00:29:24.421
walk into court and
get our butts kicked?

561
00:29:26.331 --> 00:29:28.630
You'd rather not know?

562
00:29:28.667 --> 00:29:32.695
Not if it means circumventing a
basic guaranteed right of the people.

563
00:29:32.738 --> 00:29:35.708
What about the
Supreme Court's stand

564
00:29:35.741 --> 00:29:39.143
on blind drug testing... mandatory
in certain job classifications?

565
00:29:39.177 --> 00:29:41.442
Not mandatory when you're raped.

566
00:29:49.955 --> 00:29:52.686
Monica: <i>"...It's a party."
and they started to laugh.</i>

567
00:29:52.724 --> 00:29:55.125
Doctor: <i>When they ask
where you were going.</i>

568
00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:57.425
do you look at their faces?

569
00:29:57.462 --> 00:30:00.955
Monica: <i>I think if I
look right at them.</i>

570
00:30:00.999 --> 00:30:04.868
they'll stop harassing me.

571
00:30:06.705 --> 00:30:08.901
<i>What do their faces look like?</i>

572
00:30:13.779 --> 00:30:15.748
They're young.

573
00:30:17.482 --> 00:30:19.542
Late teens.

574
00:30:19.584 --> 00:30:21.348
early 20s.

575
00:30:23.622 --> 00:30:25.955
The youngest looks frightened.

576
00:30:25.991 --> 00:30:28.517
The others are bigger.

577
00:30:29.561 --> 00:30:31.689
They seem older.

578
00:30:34.099 --> 00:30:36.330
Which one is the most...

579
00:30:36.368 --> 00:30:38.564
intimidating?

580
00:30:38.603 --> 00:30:41.129
The oldest.

581
00:30:43.542 --> 00:30:46.444
He doesn't have
any life in his eyes.

582
00:30:49.915 --> 00:30:52.475
I know he's the most dangerous.

583
00:30:55.854 --> 00:30:58.483
He doesn't care that I'm afraid.

584
00:31:00.425 --> 00:31:02.621
He's not excited by it...

585
00:31:04.596 --> 00:31:06.758
Not like the other three.

586
00:31:06.798 --> 00:31:09.393
They're there for him.

587
00:31:13.505 --> 00:31:15.974
Monica. let's back
up for a second.

588
00:31:16.007 --> 00:31:18.943
When you were
describing the boys.

589
00:31:18.977 --> 00:31:23.347
did you mean to describe
three or four to me?

590
00:31:26.051 --> 00:31:27.747
Four.

591
00:31:27.786 --> 00:31:29.846
(softly) Are you sure?

592
00:31:31.189 --> 00:31:33.283
You're sure?

593
00:31:33.325 --> 00:31:35.760
Yes.

594
00:31:41.600 --> 00:31:43.398
Now I'm going to ask you

595
00:31:43.435 --> 00:31:45.597
to relax even further.

596
00:31:45.637 --> 00:31:47.538
Remember.

597
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:50.542
these are only memories.

598
00:31:50.575 --> 00:31:53.101
They cannot hurt you.

599
00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:58.412
<i>This fourth boy.
who is the oldest.</i>

600
00:31:58.450 --> 00:32:01.113
focus in on him.

601
00:32:01.153 --> 00:32:04.180
and tell me about his face.

602
00:32:06.992 --> 00:32:08.893
Gaunt.

603
00:32:12.097 --> 00:32:13.895
Drawn.

604
00:32:13.932 --> 00:32:16.163
Looks that...

605
00:32:16.201 --> 00:32:19.171
Might once have
been good-looking.

606
00:32:21.606 --> 00:32:23.939
He has green eyes.

607
00:32:27.712 --> 00:32:30.272
He has a scar
over his right eye.

608
00:32:30.315 --> 00:32:33.342
His skin is pale.

609
00:32:34.719 --> 00:32:37.848
<i>His hair looks unwashed.</i>

610
00:32:37.889 --> 00:32:41.382
Did you. at any time
during the attack.

611
00:32:41.426 --> 00:32:44.021
hear his name used?

612
00:32:50.268 --> 00:32:52.260
Tim.

613
00:32:55.006 --> 00:32:57.032
We know there was a fourth guy.

614
00:32:57.075 --> 00:32:59.670
We know he committed
the majority of the rape.

615
00:32:59.711 --> 00:33:03.375
We got his first name. I say
we use it against the other three.

616
00:33:03.415 --> 00:33:05.509
One of them's bound to collapse.

617
00:33:05.550 --> 00:33:07.951
It would only tip our hand.

618
00:33:07.986 --> 00:33:10.046
Something in here
has got to lead to him.

619
00:33:10.088 --> 00:33:12.455
She told us who did what.

620
00:33:12.491 --> 00:33:14.392
who held her. who
performed what acts.

621
00:33:14.426 --> 00:33:16.725
the fact that he tried
to get her to fellate him.

622
00:33:16.761 --> 00:33:18.320
the threats to slash her face.

623
00:33:18.363 --> 00:33:20.594
We got everything we
need except the fourth guy.

624
00:33:20.632 --> 00:33:23.693
We pick him up. we get a blood
test to match on the semen sample.

625
00:33:23.735 --> 00:33:26.170
it's a slam dunk... The
other three go down with him.

626
00:33:26.204 --> 00:33:29.732
Fine. let's go pick him
up. His name's Tim.

627
00:33:29.774 --> 00:33:32.243
Come on. Max. you know
what the hell I'm talking about.

628
00:33:37.249 --> 00:33:39.184
All right. you want
to make a move?

629
00:33:39.217 --> 00:33:41.152
Let's check the stoop for glass.

630
00:33:41.186 --> 00:33:42.882
What?!

631
00:33:42.921 --> 00:33:45.550
She remembered
them breaking a bottle.

632
00:33:45.590 --> 00:33:48.082
threatening to
slash her face. right?

633
00:33:49.427 --> 00:33:52.158
Two months later you think
we're going to find anything?

634
00:33:52.197 --> 00:33:54.530
When's the last time you
swept under your stoop?

635
00:33:57.068 --> 00:33:59.765
Ugh. this is making me nauseous.

636
00:33:59.804 --> 00:34:02.501
Gee. that's funny. Max. You
ought to come down here.

637
00:34:02.541 --> 00:34:05.340
I was thinking of puking
just to improve the smell.

638
00:34:05.377 --> 00:34:07.505
Oop. more glass!

639
00:34:07.546 --> 00:34:10.641
<i>Okay. send it up.</i>

640
00:34:16.688 --> 00:34:19.624
Remind me never
to eat at your house.

641
00:34:19.658 --> 00:34:23.186
They're perfectly good tongs. you
think I'm going to throw them away?

642
00:34:23.228 --> 00:34:25.697
You got a couple of partials.

643
00:34:25.730 --> 00:34:28.598
third and fourth fingerprints
on one of the fragments.

644
00:34:28.633 --> 00:34:30.727
I think it's a bottleneck.

645
00:34:30.769 --> 00:34:34.900
Run a crosscheck on every set
we got. first name Tim. Timothy...

646
00:34:34.940 --> 00:34:36.602
Do all the "T's"
just to be safe.

647
00:34:36.641 --> 00:34:38.371
It's going to take some time.

648
00:34:38.410 --> 00:34:40.936
Hey. do I look
like I'm in a hurry?

649
00:34:40.979 --> 00:34:43.448
Timothy Pruiting!

650
00:34:43.481 --> 00:34:46.417
Three assaults. two narco
pops. one sale weight.

651
00:34:46.451 --> 00:34:49.114
partial matches on
middle and ring finger.

652
00:34:49.154 --> 00:34:52.318
Great. It's not enough...
They're only partial matches.

653
00:34:52.357 --> 00:34:55.657
There's at least 35 other
possible match ups here.

654
00:34:55.694 --> 00:34:57.788
Logan: <i>He lives two
blocks from the scene.</i>

655
00:34:57.829 --> 00:34:59.923
He's been popped for dealing.

656
00:34:59.965 --> 00:35:03.424
Narcotics says Metzler and Hanauer
have been running for him for months!

657
00:35:03.468 --> 00:35:05.300
Fine. The prints
place him at the scene.

658
00:35:05.337 --> 00:35:07.636
not the time. of the attack.

659
00:35:07.672 --> 00:35:09.868
We pop him. he'll
match on the DNA.

660
00:35:09.908 --> 00:35:13.640
And what if he doesn't? There's no sex
offenses here. What do we hold him on?

661
00:35:13.678 --> 00:35:16.910
I don't know. This guy fits.

662
00:35:16.948 --> 00:35:20.578
Tulli down in narcotics says
he'd gut his mother for a nickel.

663
00:35:20.619 --> 00:35:24.181
The Cutrona kid's
probably scared to death.

664
00:35:24.222 --> 00:35:26.316
Look. guys.

665
00:35:26.358 --> 00:35:28.384
do I have to speak slowly here?

666
00:35:28.426 --> 00:35:30.691
Yes. I think he's our guy.

667
00:35:30.729 --> 00:35:32.357
<i>Yes. I would like to pop him.</i>

668
00:35:32.397 --> 00:35:34.730
but this thing has been
dismissed once already.

669
00:35:34.766 --> 00:35:37.600
We cannot go off
half-cocked. We need more.

670
00:35:37.636 --> 00:35:39.628
Like what?

671
00:35:39.671 --> 00:35:43.472
Like... testimony
from the Cutrona kid.

672
00:35:43.508 --> 00:35:45.500
A statement. anything.

673
00:35:47.112 --> 00:35:48.637
We'll give him a run.

674
00:35:49.781 --> 00:35:51.773
Good. Mike. because...

675
00:35:51.816 --> 00:35:54.786
I don't think he's gonna come
waltzing in here on his own!

676
00:36:01.960 --> 00:36:03.895
Logan: We know he was there.

677
00:36:03.928 --> 00:36:06.397
We need you to
testify against him.

678
00:36:06.431 --> 00:36:10.766
You do that. the DA will reduce
the rape charges against you.

679
00:36:10.802 --> 00:36:12.464
How far? <i>You'd
have to talk to Stone.</i>

680
00:36:12.504 --> 00:36:15.167
but he assured me... no time.

681
00:36:16.574 --> 00:36:18.440
What about working for Pruiting?

682
00:36:18.476 --> 00:36:20.342
You're not up on
the drug charges.

683
00:36:20.378 --> 00:36:23.348
The hope is you clean
that up by yourself.

684
00:36:24.816 --> 00:36:26.785
He said he'd kill me.

685
00:36:26.818 --> 00:36:28.616
Max: <i>You let us
worry about that.</i>

686
00:36:28.653 --> 00:36:30.815
The truth is. he's a punk.

687
00:36:30.855 --> 00:36:33.120
He's not going to
last long in prison.

688
00:36:33.158 --> 00:36:35.127
You'd be the least
of his problems.

689
00:36:46.571 --> 00:36:48.563
He'll testify.

690
00:36:48.606 --> 00:36:49.801
(sighs)

691
00:36:55.447 --> 00:36:57.507
<i>(gun cocks)</i>

692
00:37:12.230 --> 00:37:14.790
Police. Mr. Pruiting.
You're under arrest...

693
00:37:14.833 --> 00:37:16.358
Hold it!

694
00:37:16.401 --> 00:37:19.860
Get off of me. man! You're
charged with rape and assault.

695
00:37:19.904 --> 00:37:22.100
You have the right to
remain silent... Freeze!

696
00:37:22.140 --> 00:37:24.632
Those little bastards
ratted on me. man.

697
00:37:24.676 --> 00:37:27.009
<i>I'm not going down alone!</i>

698
00:37:27.045 --> 00:37:28.809
<i>You hear me!
You think I'm lying?</i>

699
00:37:28.847 --> 00:37:31.407
<i>Those little jerks were
with me when we did it.</i>

700
00:37:31.449 --> 00:37:33.941
<i>I want those little
humps!</i> Put something on.

701
00:37:33.985 --> 00:37:37.183
Little punks'll say whatever you
want to hear! Logan: Yeah. yeah.

702
00:37:58.309 --> 00:38:00.141
<i>(knocking)</i>

703
00:38:10.755 --> 00:38:12.383
What the hell's going on?

704
00:38:12.423 --> 00:38:14.483
When was he
Mirandized at the bust?

705
00:38:14.526 --> 00:38:17.724
Hey. that's crap if he's
saying he wasn't Mirandized.

706
00:38:17.762 --> 00:38:20.288
I read 'em as we
were taking him out.

707
00:38:20.331 --> 00:38:22.891
After he made the statements.

708
00:38:22.934 --> 00:38:24.835
Are you gonna tell
us about our day?

709
00:38:24.869 --> 00:38:27.703
Sounds like spontaneous
declaration to me.

710
00:38:27.739 --> 00:38:30.573
Fine. it'll fall into "For what
it's worth." and I'll bury it.

711
00:38:30.608 --> 00:38:34.670
I'll be with my client. Let's
not have this take all day.

712
00:38:39.918 --> 00:38:41.750
Look.

713
00:38:41.786 --> 00:38:44.085
I started during his statements.

714
00:38:44.122 --> 00:38:47.251
The guy was screaming like
crazy. then the girl made a move.

715
00:38:47.292 --> 00:38:49.454
I re-read them after
everything calmed down.

716
00:38:49.494 --> 00:38:51.656
Hey. this guy was
out of his mind high.

717
00:38:51.696 --> 00:38:53.494
he was blurting
things out left and right.

718
00:38:53.531 --> 00:38:56.091
It doesn't matter. I'll
make it admissible.

719
00:38:56.134 --> 00:38:58.103
Taggert'll take
the wind out of it.

720
00:38:58.136 --> 00:39:00.731
The statements may be
too vague to help us anyway.

721
00:39:00.772 --> 00:39:03.241
So why aren't we asking
for a blood sample?

722
00:39:03.274 --> 00:39:04.742
Because we have a problem.

723
00:39:04.776 --> 00:39:06.369
Oh?

724
00:39:06.411 --> 00:39:08.277
You can't subpoena blood samples

725
00:39:08.313 --> 00:39:10.475
if you have nothing
to match it against.

726
00:39:13.284 --> 00:39:15.344
Forensics seems to have...

727
00:39:15.386 --> 00:39:17.753
misplaced the rape samples.

728
00:39:17.789 --> 00:39:19.815
What?!!

729
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:21.793
(sighs)

730
00:39:21.826 --> 00:39:23.761
This is unbelievable.

731
00:39:23.795 --> 00:39:25.764
They're continuing to
look. but my guess is

732
00:39:25.797 --> 00:39:29.325
some idiot saw the paperwork come
through on the dismissal and out they went.

733
00:39:29.367 --> 00:39:30.960
That's incredible.

734
00:39:31.002 --> 00:39:34.097
Which leaves us with not much.

735
00:39:34.138 --> 00:39:35.663
What do you want to do?

736
00:39:35.707 --> 00:39:37.869
Stone: <i>That's what
we're here to decide.</i>

737
00:39:37.909 --> 00:39:40.174
I can't justify much longer

738
00:39:40.211 --> 00:39:42.407
detaining Pruiting
to his lawyers.

739
00:39:42.447 --> 00:39:45.007
Even with the Cutrona
kid's statement?

740
00:39:45.049 --> 00:39:46.984
That's an
uncorroborated statement

741
00:39:47.018 --> 00:39:48.646
from an accomplice.

742
00:39:48.686 --> 00:39:50.951
We need something
to back that up with.

743
00:39:55.026 --> 00:39:56.927
How long can you
justify holding him?

744
00:40:00.031 --> 00:40:02.500
Duck a couple of phone
calls from his attorney.

745
00:40:02.533 --> 00:40:04.297
After that...

746
00:40:04.335 --> 00:40:06.827
After that. you
lose the paperwork.

747
00:40:06.871 --> 00:40:09.170
Max. what is this?

748
00:40:09.207 --> 00:40:12.871
Last shot... get Metzler
and Hanauer to roll.

749
00:40:12.911 --> 00:40:15.403
We got no leverage...
What the hell is going on?

750
00:40:17.482 --> 00:40:20.475
Max. no deals. I want the
other two as much as Pruiting.

751
00:40:31.029 --> 00:40:32.122
<i>(police radio chatter)</i>

752
00:40:32.163 --> 00:40:34.530
Max: <i>Look at those
mooks. still selling crack.</i>

753
00:40:39.804 --> 00:40:41.773
Gentlemen.

754
00:40:41.806 --> 00:40:44.275
If this is a roust.
you've got no cause.

755
00:40:44.309 --> 00:40:46.403
You think we need
cause. ant brain?

756
00:40:46.444 --> 00:40:49.539
You think we don't know
how to move vials. huh?

757
00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:51.708
Hey. Mike. Come on.

758
00:40:53.551 --> 00:40:56.783
No roust. no charges.
no interrogation.

759
00:40:56.821 --> 00:40:59.188
You just come in.
make some statements.

760
00:40:59.223 --> 00:41:00.953
we listen... Listen to what?

761
00:41:00.992 --> 00:41:02.858
Your version of what happened.

762
00:41:02.894 --> 00:41:05.523
Since Tim Pruiting's
been in all day screaming

763
00:41:05.563 --> 00:41:08.260
that he didn't rape
Monica DeVries. What?

764
00:41:08.299 --> 00:41:10.666
He says it was you guys.

765
00:41:10.702 --> 00:41:12.864
You're full of it.

766
00:41:12.904 --> 00:41:15.271
Watch your mouth.

767
00:41:15.306 --> 00:41:18.003
You think I pulled that
name out of thin air?

768
00:41:18.042 --> 00:41:21.410
You want me to
describe his place?

769
00:41:21.446 --> 00:41:24.291
In fact. we can drop by. I'll show you
what a mess we made during the bust.

770
00:41:24.315 --> 00:41:26.341
Is he saying we did
her? That's a load.

771
00:41:26.384 --> 00:41:28.580
Hey. you don't
have to convince us.

772
00:41:28.619 --> 00:41:30.178
we <i>know</i> he did her...

773
00:41:30.221 --> 00:41:32.986
but we gotta pop
somebody for it.

774
00:41:33.024 --> 00:41:34.686
It's bull!

775
00:41:34.726 --> 00:41:36.524
You want us to roll.

776
00:41:36.561 --> 00:41:39.360
We already arrested him. genius.

777
00:41:39.397 --> 00:41:41.491
We don't need you
to incriminate him.

778
00:41:41.532 --> 00:41:44.696
So we're not under arrest?

779
00:41:44.736 --> 00:41:46.671
Absolutely not.

780
00:41:47.772 --> 00:41:49.206
Unless...

781
00:41:49.240 --> 00:41:52.404
he convinces us that he's right.

782
00:41:56.881 --> 00:41:58.679
It can't be used against us?

783
00:41:58.716 --> 00:42:00.981
That's the deal.

784
00:42:01.019 --> 00:42:02.783
Tell you what.

785
00:42:02.820 --> 00:42:04.880
I'll make it really easy.

786
00:42:04.922 --> 00:42:07.824
I'll call Legal Aid.

787
00:42:07.859 --> 00:42:09.828
They'll set up a room.

788
00:42:09.861 --> 00:42:12.695
You come in. in and out.

789
00:42:12.730 --> 00:42:16.258
no hanging around.
Give me a quarter.

790
00:42:16.300 --> 00:42:18.394
What? Give me a quarter.

791
00:42:21.172 --> 00:42:22.731
What are you doing?

792
00:42:22.774 --> 00:42:24.675
Huh?

793
00:42:31.249 --> 00:42:34.686
Hey. that's great. Max. Now we
got even more unusable statements.

794
00:42:34.719 --> 00:42:37.188
Think so? <i>Who you calling?</i>

795
00:42:38.256 --> 00:42:39.622
Marie.

796
00:42:42.760 --> 00:42:46.595
Think they have a reasonable
expectation of privacy right now?

797
00:42:48.332 --> 00:42:50.130
Hi. honey. it's me.

798
00:42:50.168 --> 00:42:51.966
<i>I'll probably be late tonight.</i>

799
00:42:55.740 --> 00:42:57.766
You're out of your
mind. you know that?

800
00:42:57.809 --> 00:42:59.801
Stone's going to
blow a fuse over this

801
00:42:59.844 --> 00:43:01.836
and Cragen'll strap
us to our desks forever.

802
00:43:01.879 --> 00:43:03.677
Wrong. Detective.

803
00:43:03.714 --> 00:43:07.446
They are <i>not</i> under arrest.

804
00:43:09.020 --> 00:43:10.511
Oooh.

805
00:43:10.555 --> 00:43:13.582
Hanauer's voice: <i>Because
if he is. I'm not taking the fall.</i>

806
00:43:13.624 --> 00:43:16.526
<i>and neither should you. We
didn't do her. He got off on it.</i>

807
00:43:16.561 --> 00:43:19.292
Metzler: <i>What's all this crap
about keeping our mouth's shut?</i>

808
00:43:19.330 --> 00:43:21.299
<i>He tells us they got no evidence</i>

809
00:43:21.332 --> 00:43:23.733
<i>'cause he's the only
one who'll match the load.</i>

810
00:43:23.768 --> 00:43:26.260
<i>and he gets picked up
and rolls? Screw him!</i>

811
00:43:26.304 --> 00:43:28.864
<i>Look. we know what we
did. we just tell it straight.</i>

812
00:43:28.906 --> 00:43:31.740
<i>All we did was hold her.
maybe some other stupid stuff.</i>

813
00:43:31.776 --> 00:43:34.211
<i>but we're not riding
down for Pruiting.</i>

814
00:43:34.245 --> 00:43:36.180
All right. so it's damning.

815
00:43:36.214 --> 00:43:39.082
<i>Do I have to run
a list here. Stone?</i>

816
00:43:39.117 --> 00:43:42.679
Miranda. Bartolameo. the
Supreme Court's Minnick decision.

817
00:43:42.720 --> 00:43:44.882
The whole thing's
illegally obtained.

818
00:43:44.922 --> 00:43:46.584
They were both
represented by counsel.

819
00:43:46.624 --> 00:43:48.650
Not for the past two
months. they weren't.

820
00:43:48.693 --> 00:43:51.993
There were no charges pending. There
was no accusatory instrument pending.

821
00:43:52.029 --> 00:43:54.396
no outstanding indictment.
You know as well as I do

822
00:43:54.432 --> 00:43:56.663
that Minnick provides
nothing new in New York.

823
00:43:56.701 --> 00:43:58.465
What about their privacy?

824
00:44:00.204 --> 00:44:03.800
The court's stance on the
expectation of privacy is fairly clear.

825
00:44:03.841 --> 00:44:07.073
Please! They were
sitting in a cop car.

826
00:44:07.111 --> 00:44:11.139
With the doors wide open. in the
middle of the day. in a city street.

827
00:44:11.182 --> 00:44:15.119
You think there's a greater expectation
of privacy there than on a cordless phone?

828
00:44:15.153 --> 00:44:17.918
<i>And I'm sure you know
the court's stance on that.</i>

829
00:44:17.955 --> 00:44:19.753
It's debatable.

830
00:44:19.790 --> 00:44:22.055
That's not debatable.
that's precedent.

831
00:44:22.093 --> 00:44:24.653
And that's what I'm
going into court with.

832
00:44:24.695 --> 00:44:26.664
You did good work.

833
00:44:26.697 --> 00:44:29.189
Make sure it doesn't
get thrown out of court.

834
00:44:29.233 --> 00:44:31.998
I can't be sure of anything.
but I do know what I believe in.

835
00:44:32.036 --> 00:44:34.232
and I believe you
didn't violate the system.

836
00:44:34.272 --> 00:44:36.366
Want to re-arrest
Hanauer and Metzler?

837
00:44:36.407 --> 00:44:39.241
Absolutely. No bargains.
The charge is rape.

838
00:44:39.310 --> 00:44:42.280
We'll let their defense attorneys
figure out if they want to sever or not.

839
00:44:42.313 --> 00:44:44.214
I'm sure they know
the procedure by now.

840
00:44:44.248 --> 00:44:46.342
What do you want to
do with the Cutrona kid?

841
00:44:46.384 --> 00:44:49.877
Him we need. Paul's going
to bring him in for a statement.

842
00:44:49.921 --> 00:44:52.413
I can use that instead
of the DNA match.

843
00:44:52.456 --> 00:44:54.118
Well. our boy Pruiting

844
00:44:54.158 --> 00:44:56.889
just tried to sell everyone
he knows during booking...

845
00:44:56.928 --> 00:44:59.193
Crack dealers. peepers...

846
00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:01.131
All in the hopes
of landing a deal.

847
00:45:01.165 --> 00:45:03.760
Hell of a guy.

848
00:45:03.801 --> 00:45:05.360
Quite a piece of work.

849
00:45:07.171 --> 00:45:10.573
In the coming days. you will hear
arguments on whether three men

850
00:45:10.608 --> 00:45:13.578
in this courtroom are
guilty of the crime of rape.

851
00:45:13.611 --> 00:45:17.207
You will then be asked
to decide two things:

852
00:45:17.248 --> 00:45:18.978
the fate of the defendants.

853
00:45:19.016 --> 00:45:22.111
and more indirectly the
fate of a legal system.

854
00:45:22.153 --> 00:45:26.318
A system that is too often
circumvented and mocked

855
00:45:26.357 --> 00:45:29.521
<i>by those who seek to
escape the weight of justice.</i>

856
00:45:29.560 --> 00:45:34.191
A system which can
be used by the defense

857
00:45:34.232 --> 00:45:38.260
to put a woman.
violated against her will.

858
00:45:38.302 --> 00:45:40.032
on trial...

859
00:45:40.071 --> 00:45:43.007
for anything ranging
from how she was dressed

860
00:45:43.040 --> 00:45:46.238
to why she was in a
particular neighborhood.

861
00:45:51.882 --> 00:45:53.783
It is the State's position

862
00:45:53.818 --> 00:45:55.980
that there are no
valid reasons to justify

863
00:45:56.020 --> 00:45:58.819
violent sexual behavior
against another person's will.

864
00:45:58.856 --> 00:46:02.156
<i>It is my job to present
these facts to you</i>

865
00:46:02.193 --> 00:46:05.288
and hope that you will
agree with the State's position.

866
00:46:05.329 --> 00:46:08.231
It is your job to listen...

867
00:46:08.266 --> 00:46:10.826
To listen how. through
willful intimidation.

868
00:46:10.868 --> 00:46:13.633
<i>and a moderate knowledge
of the legal system.</i>

869
00:46:13.671 --> 00:46:15.663
<i>these three men</i>

870
00:46:15.706 --> 00:46:17.937
chose to flaunt
their crime of rape

871
00:46:17.975 --> 00:46:18.999
in the face of a woman...

872
00:46:23.114 --> 00:46:25.083
And in the face of this system.

873
00:46:49.373 --> 00:46:52.673
<i>(theme music playing)</i>
